This article discusses the economic partnership between the United States and Turkey. It highlights the growth in bilateral trade and investment between the two countries in recent years. The Framework for Strategic Economic & Commercial Cooperation (FSECC) was established in 2009 to strengthen economic ties between the two nations. The article also mentions the potential impact of the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (T-TIP) between the US and the European Union on Turkey. Cooperation in clean energy is emphasized, with the United States and Turkey working together to develop the clean energy sector in Turkey. The article also mentions collaboration in the innovation economy, with a focus on priority sectors such as healthcare, pharmaceuticals, and information technology. The importance of forging alliances between US and Turkish companies is highlighted, with examples of successful joint ventures. The article concludes by expressing optimism for the future of US-Turkish economic relations.